---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const pageTitle = "About | Scott Gruber";
const pageDescription = "Learn more about the person behind the analytics.";
---

<BaseLayout title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription}>
  <article class="max-w-5xl mx-auto py-12">
    
    <header class="mb-16">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold tracking-tighter text-zinc-900 mb-6">
        Beyond the data.
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-zinc-500 font-medium leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
        I believe the best technical architectures are built by people who understand how to communicate with humans first.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 gap-12 items-start">
      
      {/* The Content */}
      <div class="md:col-span-7 prose prose-zinc prose-lg max-w-none 
                  prose-h2:text-2xl prose-h2:tracking-tight prose-h2:mt-12
                  prose-p:text-zinc-600 prose-p:leading-relaxed">
        
        <p>
          My journey into technical analytics didn't start in a computer science lab—it started in Journalism and Political Science at Rutgers University. That background taught me how to ask the right questions, investigate anomalies, and most importantly, translate complex findings into stories that drive action.
        </p>

        <h2>The Bridge Between Tech and Marketing</h2>
        <p>
          Over the past 8 years, I've found my niche acting as the translator between marketing visionaries and backend engineers. Whether it's repairing broken API integrations, migrating legacy CMS platforms, or writing Python scripts to automate tedious reporting, my goal is always the same: remove the friction so teams can do their best work.
        </p>

        <h2>Offline Pursuits</h2>
        <p>
          I'm a big believer in continuous learning. Recently, I've been studying Korean (currently TOPIK Level 2) to challenge myself in a completely different linguistic framework. 
        </p>
        <p>
          When I'm not auditing GA4 properties or architecting BigQuery databases, you can often find me giving back to the local community as a substitute teacher in the Manville, NJ area—a role that keeps my presentation and adaptability skills incredibly sharp.
        </p>
        
        <div class="mt-12 not-prose">
          <a href="/contact" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center bg-blue-600 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-full text-sm font-medium hover:bg-blue-700 transition-colors">
            Let's connect
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* The Image (Placeholder) */}
      <div class="md:col-span-5 md:sticky md:top-24">
        <div class="aspect-[4/5] bg-zinc-100 rounded-3xl overflow-hidden border border-zinc-200 relative">
          {/* Replace this div with an actual <img /> or Astro <Image /> component later */}
          <div class="absolute inset-0 flex flex-col items-center justify-center text-zinc-400 p-8 text-center">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" class="w-12 h-12 mb-4 opacity-50">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M15.75 6a3.75 3.75 0 11-7.5 0 3.75 3.75 0 017.5 0zM4.501 20.118a7.5 7.5 0 0114.998 0A17.933 17.933 0 0112 21.75c-2.676 0-5.216-.584-7.499-1.632z" />
            </svg>
            <span class="text-sm font-medium">Drop your headshot here.<br/>(Recommend 800x1000px)</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>